---
import TestLayout from "../layouts/TestLayout.astro";
---

<TestLayout 
  title="Frequently Asked Questions | 16 Personality Test" 
  description="Get answers to common questions about personality tests, how they work, and how to use your results."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 py-12 sm:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-[-2.4px] text-ink sm:text-5xl dark:text-on-primary">
      Frequently Asked Questions
    </h1>
    
    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-body dark:text-mute">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">How long does the test take?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">The test consists of 48 questions and typically takes about 5 minutes to complete. You can save your progress and return later if needed.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Are the results accurate?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">The test is designed to provide meaningful insights into your personality preferences. While no online test can capture the full complexity of human personality, our assessment is based on well-established personality frameworks and professionally written questions.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Can my personality change?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Your core personality preferences tend to remain stable throughout your life, though you may develop greater flexibility in using different aspects of your personality as you grow and gain experience.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Is the test free?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Yes, the 16 Personality Test is completely free to take. There are no hidden charges or premium results.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Do I need to create an account?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">No account is required. Your progress is saved locally in your browser, and you can access your results without signing up.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">What if I get a balanced result?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">A balanced result means you scored close to the middle on one or more dimensions. This indicates you can comfortably use both preferences depending on the situation, which is a sign of psychological flexibility.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">How should I use my results?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Use your results as a starting point for self-reflection. Consider how your preferences show up in your daily life, relationships, and work. The goal is greater self-awareness, not putting yourself in a box.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</TestLayout>
